             <ol>
                 <li>Lie on your belly on your mat, with a blanket under your pelvis if needed. Press all of your toes into the floor and then bend your knees, keeping the toes active.
                 </li>
                 <li>Grab the outer edges of your ankles with your hands and flex your feet strongly.</li>
                 <li>On an inhalation, lift your rib cage and shoulders toward your ears. On an exhalation, lengthen your tailbone and kick your legs back into your hands as you hold on firmly</li>
                 <li>From here, lift your head and heart. Gaze forward. Extend through the roof of your mouth and crown of your head. As you do so, always keep strong energy moving from the base of your spine through the crown of your head to help support
                 </li>
                 <li>Stay lifted for 5 breaths</li>
             </ol>
